cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a new architecture for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image synthesis using Capsule Networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the advantages of Capsule Networks over Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in image synthesis, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves training GANs, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Capsule Networks also involves neural networks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the results of different architectures, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics).
